<activity xml:id="act-Terms">
    <title>Thinking about the Terms of a Series</title>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                What does it mean for the series <m>\displaystyle\sum_{k=1}^\infty a_k</m> to converge?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
            <p>
                If you need a reminder, take a look back at <xref ref="def-SeriesConvergence" text="type-global-title"/>
            </p>
        </hint>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Calculate the difference between <m>S_{n+1}=\displaystyle \sum_{k=1}^{n+1} a_k</m> and <m>S_{n}=\displaystyle \sum_{k=1}^{n} a_k</m>, <m>S_{n+1}-S_n</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                If the sequence of partial sums for a series, <m>\{S_n\}_{n=1}^\infty</m> converges, then what should we expect to happen with the values of <m>S_{n+1}</m> and <m>S_n</m>? What does this mean for the difference <m>S_{n+1}-S_n</m>?
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Now consider a series that we know diverges, the <xref ref="def-HarmonicSeries" text="title"/>. Find the limit,
                <me>
                    \lim_{k\to\infty} \frac{1}{k}
                </me>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
</activity>